This paper deals with conceptual modeling and querying of relational data, which are core topics in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also addresses the problem of incomplete data, which is a common issue in data integration and can be tackled using techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cardinality constraints and disjointness assertions involves logical reasoning, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). The query answering algorithm proposed in the paper involves recursive Datalog queries, which are a type of data structure used in computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also touches upon the topic of software engineering, as it proposes an algorithm for query answering (cs.SE).
